                     WELCOME TO THE RANGER'S GUILD!
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Congratulations! You are now a Ranger, a guardian of the wild places
of Darkwind. The Wind speaks to you now, connecting you to all Rangers
across the land. This guide will help you get started.

FIRST STEPS (do these immediately):
------------------------------------
1. SET YOUR TERRAINS AND ENEMY. You cannot advance until these are set.
   These are permanent choices that define your Ranger, so choose wisely.
   Type each command with no argument to see your options:

     setprime           Choose your primary terrain (biggest bonuses)
     setsecond          Choose your secondary terrain (smaller bonuses)
     setenemy           Choose your enemy species (combat bonuses vs them)

   Example: setprime forest, setsecond mountain, setenemy bear

2. LEARN YOUR FIRST SKILL. You start knowing 'forage' but haven't
   learned it yet. Type 'learn forage' to learn it. This unlocks
   more skills you can learn. Type 'skilltree' to see all skills
   and how they connect.

3. GET TO THE WILDERNESS. Ranger skills only work outside of cities.
   Head out of town to start using your abilities.

HOW RANGERS WORK:
-----------------
- You earn Ranger XP in battle and gain guild levels automatically. Type
  'cost', 'radvance guild', or 'gscore ranger' to see your progress.
- Spend slots to LEARN skills (type 'learn' to see what's
  available, 'learn <skill>' to learn one).
- Skills have TERRAIN requirements - some only work in certain places.
  Type 'check <terrain>' to see what works where.
- Your PRIMARY terrain gives +20% damage, -20% SP cost, -20% cooldown.
  Your SECONDARY terrain gives +10% to those same things.
- Fighting your ENEMY SPECIES gives +30% critical hit chance.

ESSENTIAL COMMANDS:
-------------------
ranhelp / rh         Full help system. 'rh <topic>' for details.
skilltree / tree     View the entire skill tree and your progress.
learn                See available skills and learn new ones.
skills / myskills    See your learned skills.
slots                See your available slots.
cost / tally         See character costs and Ranger XP progress.
improve <stat>       Advance stats, or show Ranger XP with 'improve guild'.
rscore / rsc         Your full Ranger status report.
rangers              See who else is online.
ran <message>        Chat with other Rangers.

GETTING AROUND:
---------------
The Ranger's Lodge is in the deep forest southwest of Darkwind.
From town, go to the forest (west from Village Road area) and
keep heading deeper. When you reach the deep forest, go northeast
to find the forest meadow, then northeast again to the Lodge.

Type 'rh' for the full command list, or 'rh <topic>' for help
on any topic. Good luck, Ranger!
